TITLE: Oracle comes up short on revenue but touts AI cloud contracts
SUMMARY: Larry Ellison pointed to a doubling in the amount of money that artificial intelligence development companies have agreed to spend on Oracle cloud services

TITLE: Lululemon ups guidance after 'strong' growth in China boosts quarterly sales
SUMMARY: Lululemon raised its full year guidance and saw its sales and profit rise 18% during its most recent quarter, fueled by a 61% boost in China.

TITLE: Polestar second-quarter loss widens as it ramps up EV deliveries
SUMMARY: Polestar is still on track to build 60,000 to 70,000 EVs in 2023, with two new models coming in the next several months.

TITLE: UBS shares jump to 2008 highs after profit beat, job cuts announcement
SUMMARY: UBS posted second-quarter profit of $28.9 billion in its first quarterly earnings since Switzerland's largest bank completed its takeover of Credit Suisse.

TITLE: Buy now, pay later firm Klarna cuts losses in first half but fails to post profit
SUMMARY: Swedish buy now, pay later firm Klarna reduced losses by roughly 67% in the first half of 2023, as it cut costs dramatically in a bid for profitability.

TITLE: Salesforce shares pop on earnings beat and optimistic forecast
SUMMARY: Salesforce saw gains in all five product categories, and CEO Marc Benioff sees more growth from artificial intelligence capabilities

TITLE: Jack Daniel's maker Brown-Forman reports lagging whiskey sales, narrower profit
SUMMARY: The company saw some growth across its ready-to-drink and tequila categories, but whiskey sales lagged.

TITLE: Shares of HP fall 6% following revenue miss
SUMMARY: Shares of HP fell Wednesday after the company missed analysts' expectations for revenue.

TITLE: Lego sales increase while other toy makers struggle
SUMMARY: While other toy companies have been hammered by a slump in toy demand this year, Lego is one of the few to post positive gains.

TITLE: Nio reports wider second-quarter loss amid China slowdown and product line revamp
SUMMARY: Nio's second-quarter loss widened from a year ago, as it overhauled key products amid an economic slowdown in China. But deliveries are already rebounding.

TITLE: Best Buy scales back sales outlook as results top expectations
SUMMARY: While Best Buy trimmed its sales guidance for the year, it raised the bottom end of its profit outlook.

TITLE: Shares of BYD jump after Chinese EV maker posts 200% surge in first half profit
SUMMARY: Chinese automaker BYD on Monday posted a 204.68% jump in profit in the first half of the year driven by record deliveries.

TITLE: Shares of China's food delivery leader Meituan fall more than 5% on weaker Q3 outlook
SUMMARY: Meituan shares fell 5% Friday after CEO Wang Xing warned of a food delivery slowdown in the third quarter during the firm's latest earnings call on Thursday.

TITLE: Gap reports another period of declining sales across all brands, warns of 'uncertain consumer'
SUMMARY: Gap reported mixed results on Thursday and underwhelming current-quarter guidance.

TITLE: Nordstrom tops Wall Streetâ€™s quarterly expectations, even as it braces for sales declines
SUMMARY: The department store retailer stuck by its forecast for the full year, despite better-than-expected results.

TITLE: Dollar Tree's shares sink 13%, as CEO says 'challenging' economy is pressuring discounter
SUMMARY: Dollar Tree raised its sales outlook for the year but narrowed its earnings guidance.

TITLE: Australia's Qantas delivers record profit, reveals plans to increase international fleet
SUMMARY: Australia's Qantas announced a record annual profit on Thursday, and announced a share buyback and a multi-billion dollar order for 24 new aircrafts.

TITLE: Nvidia tops estimates and says sales will jump 170% this quarter, driven by demand for AI chips
SUMMARY: Revenue in the second quarter doubled from $6.7 billion a year earlier and increased 88% from the prior period.

TITLE: Abercrombie & Fitch shares soar 23% as retailer blows past earnings estimates, raises guidance
SUMMARY: Abercrombie & Fitch has posted strong sales, even as other retailers see a weaker and choosier consumer.

TITLE: Peloton shares drop 22% after posting wider-than-expected loss, falling sales due to Bike recall, seasonality
SUMMARY: Peloton's shares plunged 22% after the company posted a wider-than-expected loss and churn that it blamed on its Bike seat recall and seasonality.

TITLE: Foot Locker shares plunge 28% as it slashes guidance and blames 'consumer softness'
SUMMARY: Athletic apparel retailer Foot Locker reported another quarterly sales decline and missed revenue expectations as consumers continue to pull back from shoes.

TITLE: Macy's shares drop 14% as retailer says consumers will be cautious the rest of the year
SUMMARY: Macy's topped adjusted earnings and sales estimates, but said revenue fell year over year and reiterated a cautious forecast.

TITLE: Dick's shares fall 24% as retailer slashes outlook over theft concerns
SUMMARY: Dick's Sporting Goods says it's grappling with an uptick in retail theft that contributed to a 23% drop in profits, prompting it to slash its full year outlook.

TITLE: Lowe's sticks by full-year earnings forecast despite weakening sales, as spring projects offer a boost
SUMMARY: CEO Marvin Ellison told CNBC that shakier consumer confidence is leading to softer discretionary sales.

TITLE: China's Baidu reports 15% revenue growth, beating expectations
SUMMARY: Chinese tech company Baidu reported better-than-expected revenue, up by 15% year-on-year in the second quarter.

TITLE: Zoom beats expectations and lifts full-year guidance on enterprise business strength
SUMMARY: While the consumer part of Zoom doesn't look as strong as it once did, the enterprise side looks robust enough for executives to raise their forecast.

TITLE: Palo Alto shares rise on earnings beat, surprising investors who worried about a Friday report
SUMMARY: Palo Alto's better-than-expected earnings report was a relief to investors who were concerned about potentially bad numbers due to a late Friday announcement

TITLE: Walmart raises full-year earnings forecast as grocery, online growth fuel higher sales
SUMMARY: Walmart beat earnings and revenue expectations as it capitalizes on its low-priced reputation with consumers looking for value.

TITLE: Europe's Stripe rival Adyen dives 39% after slowest sales growth on record
SUMMARY: Adyen reported revenue of 739.1 million euros ($804.3 million) in the first half of the year, up by 21% from 2022, but below analyst estimates.

TITLE: Shoppers are spending big at T.J. Maxx, HomeGoods as Target sales slide
SUMMARY: TJX Cos., which runs T.J. Maxx and Marshalls, is seeing big gains in discretionary purchases as cash-strapped consumers look for a deal amid high inflation.
